questions.question: If $\overrightarrow{\mathrm{a}}$ is a nonzero vector such that its projections on the vectors $2 \hat{i}-\hat{j}+2 \hat{k}, \hat{i}+2 \hat{j}-2 \hat{k}$ and $\hat{k}$ are equal, then a unit vector along $\overrightarrow{\mathrm{a}}$ is :

$$ \begin{array}{l} \text{Match List I with List II} \\ \\ \begin{array}{|c|l|c|l|} \hline & \text{LIST I} & & \text{LIST II} \\ \hline \text{A.} & \text{Angular momentum} & \text{I.} & [\mathrm{ML}^{2} \mathrm{~T}^{-2}] \\ \text{B.} & \text{Torque} & \text{II.} & [\mathrm{ML}^{-2} \mathrm{~T}^{-2}] \\ \text{C.} & \text{Stress} & \text{III} & [\mathrm{ML}^{2} \mathrm{~T}^{-1}] \\ \text{D.} & \text{Pressure gradient} & \text{IV.} & [\mathrm{ML}^{-1} \mathrm{~T}^{-2}] \\ \hline \end{array} \\ \\ \text{Choose the correct answer from the options given below:} \end{array} $$
questions.option_a: A - I, B - IV, C - III, D - II
questions.option_b: A - III, B - I, C - IV, D - II
questions.option_c: A - IV, B - II, C - I, D - III
questions.option_d: A - II, B - III, C - IV, D - I
